text: Witham is a constituency in the House of Commons of the UK Parliament. It was created in 2010. Since then it has been represented by Priti Patel. Patel is a member of the Conservative Party. She was the Home Secretary between 2019 and 2022 in the cabinet of Boris Johnson. == History == The constituency was made in 2010 following changes to the borders of constituencies in Essex. ==Members of Parliament== Election Member Party 2010 Priti Patel Conservative ==Elections== == References == Category:Westminster Parliamentary constituencies in England Category:Essex
